<caption id="DF2666424A07271ED2FCB9A3FD87F811" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5147151" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5147151" box="[136,596,2006,2028]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5147151/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" startId="2.[136,229,2006,2028]" targetBox="[178,1412,175,1989]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8BE636CA4A07271ED2FCB9A3FD87F811" blockId="2.[136,596,2006,2028]" box="[136,596,2006,2028]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A07271ED2FCB9A3FF2DF816" bold="true" box="[136,254,2006,2028]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A07271ED377B9A2FE34F811" authorityName="Di Grist., Gottschl. &amp; Raimondo" authorityYear="2014" box="[259,487,2007,2028]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terraccianoi">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A07271ED377B9A2FE34F811" box="[259,487,2007,2028]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Hieracium terraccianoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: Holotype.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C34365414A06271FD2C9BEEBFBC0FED9" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE636CA4A06271FD2C9BEEBFCF6FF20" blockId="3.[136,1452,158,293]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD2C9BEEBFEEDFF45" bold="true" box="[189,318,158,184]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Etymology</emphasis>
:—The new species is dedicated to Nicola Terracciano (1837–1921), Neapolitan botanist who devoted his work especially to the floristic study of the Pollino area.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE636CA4A06271FD2C9BE93FCC3FEFD" blockId="3.[136,1452,158,293]" box="[189,784,230,256]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD2C9BE93FEA5FEFD" bold="true" box="[189,374,230,256]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Biological form</emphasis>
:—Pseudorosulate hemicryptophyte.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE636CA4A06271FD2C9BF7FFBC0FED9" blockId="3.[136,1452,158,293]" box="[189,1043,266,293]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD2C9BF7FFEEAFED9" bold="true" box="[189,313,266,292]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Phenology</emphasis>
:—Flowering June to mid-July; fruiting in June and July (
<figureCitation id="13622A4F4A06271FD1B5BF7FFBD6FED9" box="[961,1029,266,292]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1192,1214]" captionTargetBox="[227,1361,317,1168]" captionTargetId="figure-61@3.[227,1361,317,1168]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hieracium terraccianoi fruiting in nature." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5147153" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5147153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF2666424A06271FD2FCBADDFD45FB43" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5147153" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5147153" box="[136,662,1192,1214]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5147153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" startId="3.[136,229,1192,1214]" targetBox="[227,1361,317,1168]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BE636CA4A06271FD2FCBADDFD45FB43" blockId="3.[136,662,1192,1214]" box="[136,662,1192,1214]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD2FCBADDFF2DFB40" bold="true" box="[136,254,1192,1214]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A06271FD377BADCFE34FB43" authorityName="Di Grist., Gottschl. &amp; Raimondo" authorityYear="2014" box="[259,487,1193,1214]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terraccianoi">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD377BADCFE34FB43" box="[259,487,1193,1214]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Hieracium terraccianoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fruiting in nature.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C34365414A062718D2C9BA99FA70FAC6" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BE636CA4A06271FD2C9BA99FE48FA46" blockId="3.[136,1452,1260,2079]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD2C9BA99FE39FAFA" bold="true" box="[189,490,1260,1287]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A06271FD079BA9BFCCAFAFA" authorityName="Di Grist., Gottschl. &amp; Raimondo" authorityYear="2014" box="[525,793,1262,1287]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terraccianoi">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD079BA9BFCCAFAFA" box="[525,793,1262,1287]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Hieracium terraccianoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in a restricted area between 1320 and 
<quantity id="4CA19B2F4A06271FD746BA98FA59FAFA" box="[1330,1418,1261,1288]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" unit="m" value="1450.0">1450 m</quantity>
of elevation, at the Scala di Gaudolino (Pollino Massif), Morano Calabro (Cosenza province), in the Pollino National Park (
<figureCitation id="13622A4F4A06271FD2BABB40FEC0FAB2" box="[206,275,1333,1359]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,229,2027,2049]" captionTargetBox="[214,1373,929,2002]" captionTargetId="figure-395@1.[214,1373,929,2002]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. The single known location of Hieracium terraccianoi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5147149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5147149/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). From a bioclimatic point of view, according to the terminology of Rivas-Martinez (1981), the area falls within the supramediterranean bioclimatic belt with the lower humid ombrotype. 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A06271FD619BB2FFAABFA8E" authorityName="Di Grist., Gottschl. &amp; Raimondo" authorityYear="2014" box="[1133,1400,1370,1395]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terraccianoi">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD619BB2FFAABFA8E" box="[1133,1400,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Hieracium terraccianoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a calcicolous taxon, represented by about 300 individuals growing on NW-facing rocks and stony slopes, in clearings of the beech forest (
<figureCitation id="13622A4F4A06271FD33DBBD4FE5DFA46" box="[329,398,1441,1467]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1065,1087]" captionTargetBox="[227,1361,190,1041]" captionTargetId="figure-29@4.[227,1361,190,1041]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Carbonate rocks and stony slopes of Scala di Gaudolino, the habitat of Hieracium terraccianoi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5147155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5147155/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE636CA4A06271FD2C9BBB1FBE5F9F9" blockId="3.[136,1452,1260,2079]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD2C9BBB1FE79FA22" bold="true" box="[189,426,1476,1503]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Conservation status</emphasis>
:—According to the 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3B4A06271FD0FABBB0FCF7FA22" author="IUCN" box="[654,804,1477,1503]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" refId="ref2966" refString="IUCN (2010) The IUCN Red List of threatened species, version 2010.4. IUCN Red List Unit, Cambridge, UK. Available: http: // www. iucnredlist. org. (accessed 25 May 2013)." type="url" year="2010">IUCN (2010)</bibRefCitation>
criteria for the conservation status assessment, 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A06271FD740BBB3FEC1F9FE" authorityName="Di Grist., Gottschl. &amp; Raimondo" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terraccianoi">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD740BBB3FEC1F9FE" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Hieracium terraccianoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be classified as “Critically Endangered” (CR): B1a+2a; C2a(ii).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE636CA4A06271FD2C9B879FA81F7E2" blockId="3.[136,1452,1260,2079]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD2C9B879FE0FF9DB" bold="true" box="[189,476,1548,1574]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Taxonomic relationship</emphasis>
:—Bract indumentum (appearing greyish because of the presence of many stellate hairs and but few glandular hairs) and the bluish green, spotted leaves suggest a possible relationship of 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A06271FD740B847FEC1F992" authorityName="Di Grist., Gottschl. &amp; Raimondo" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terraccianoi">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD740B847FEC1F992" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Hieracium terraccianoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with species of 
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD3B3B823FE30F992" box="[455,483,1622,1647]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">H.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A06271FD057B820FB47F98D" authority="(Arvet-Touvet 1880: 287) Clapham (1952: 1153)" authorityName="Clapham" authorityPageNumber="1153" authorityYear="1952" baseAuthorityName="Arvet-Touvet" baseAuthorityPageNumber="287" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[547,1172,1621,1648]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Cystocloniaceae" genus="Bifida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gigartinales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD057B820FDB4F992" box="[547,615,1621,1647]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Bifida</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3B4A06271FD001B820FC55F992" author="Arvet-Touvet, C." box="[629,902,1621,1647]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" pagination="278 - 292" refId="ref2092" refString="Arvet-Touvet, C. (1880) Essai de classification sur les genres Pilosella &amp; Hieracium. Bulletin de la Societe Dauphinoise pour l'Echange des Plantes 7: 278 - 292." type="journal article" year="1880">Arvet-Touvet 1880: 287</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3B4A06271FD1E1B820FB47F98D" author="Clapham, A. R. &amp; Tutin, T. G. &amp; Warburg, E. F." box="[917,1172,1621,1648]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" refId="ref2339" refString="Clapham, A. R., Tutin, T. G. &amp; Warburg, E. F. (1952) Flora of the British Isles. University Press, Cambridge, 1591 pp." type="book" year="1952">Clapham (1952: 1153)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The long narrowed base of the basal leaves and the presence of 2, sometimes 3 stem leaves (with the lowest stem leaf often being inserted only 
<quantity id="4CA19B2F4A06271FD2FCB8E8FF0EF94A" box="[136,221,1693,1719]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" unit="cm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 cm</quantity>
above the rosette leaves) show some similarity with 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A06271FD134B8EBFAEBF94A" authority="(Fries 1819: 76) Fries (1845: 7)" authorityName="Fries" authorityPageNumber="7" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="Fries" baseAuthorityPageNumber="76" baseAuthorityYear="1819" box="[832,1336,1693,1720]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caesium">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD134B8EBFC13F94A" box="[832,960,1694,1719]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">H. caesium</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3B4A06271FD1A5B8E8FBAAF945" author="Fries, E." box="[977,1145,1693,1720]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" pagination="73 - 80" refId="ref2495" refString="Fries, E. (1819) Novitiae Florae Svecicae. Part V. Continuatio. Berlingianis, Lund, pp. 73 - 80." type="book chapter" year="1819">Fries 1819: 76</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3B4A06271FD6FEB8E8FAEBF94A" author="Fries, E." box="[1162,1336,1693,1720]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" refId="ref2521" refString="Fries, E. (1845) Summa Vegetabilium Scandinaviae. Typographia Academica, Uppsala, 258 pp." type="book" year="1845">Fries (1845: 7)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A06271FD2FCB8B7FED9F926" authorityName="Fries" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="Fries" baseAuthorityYear="1819" box="[136,266,1730,1755]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caesium">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD2FCB8B7FED9F926" box="[136,266,1730,1755]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">H. caesium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has its main distribution in N Europe, where it has evolved postglacially. Direct relationship across a disjunction between N Europe and 
<collectingRegion id="499DF8284A06271FD061B890FDA4F902" box="[533,631,1765,1791]" country="Italy" name="Calabria" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Calabria</collectingRegion>
, implying a relict state for 
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD1D2B893FB89F902" box="[934,1114,1766,1791]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A06271FD1D2B893FB85F902" authorityName="Di Grist., Gottschl. &amp; Raimondo" authorityYear="2014" box="[934,1110,1766,1791]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terraccianoi">H. terraccianoi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
is an improbable assumption. Therefore the morphological traits suggesting such an affinity (number of stem leaves, bract indumentum) result from analogy. The winged petioles of the lower stem leaf and the semiamplexicaul base of the upper stem leaf (
<figureCitation id="13622A4F4A06271FD741B958FAAAF8BA" box="[1333,1401,1837,1863]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[136,229,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[178,1412,175,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-29@2.[176,1412,175,1989]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hieracium terraccianoi: Holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5147151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5147151/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) are more important features, as they indicate membership in 
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD16CB927FCE7F896" box="[792,820,1874,1899]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">H.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD10CB924FC29F896" box="[888,1018,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Grovesiana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3B4A06271FD677B924FAF0F891" author="Gottschlich, G." box="[1027,1315,1873,1900]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 328" refId="ref2675" refString="Gottschlich, G. (2009 a) Die Gattung Hieracium L. (Compositae) in der Region Abruzzen (Italien). Eine floristisch-taxonomische Studie. Stapfia 89: 1 - 328." type="journal article" year="2009">Gottschlich (2009a: 152)</bibRefCitation>
. The Italian endemic 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A06271FD284B903FDA0F872" authority="Belli (1897: 491)" authorityName="Belli" authorityPageNumber="491" authorityYear="1897" box="[240,627,1909,1935]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grovesianum">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD284B903FE76F872" box="[240,421,1910,1935]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">H. grovesianum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3B4A06271FD3D9B900FDA0F872" author="Belli, S." box="[429,627,1909,1935]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" pagination="421 - 499" refId="ref2151" refString="Belli, S. (1897) Hieracium di Sardegna. [ser. 2] Memorie della Reale Accademia delle Scienze di Torino 47: 421 - 499." type="journal article" year="1897">Belli (1897: 491)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is the most representative taxon of that section. It is a variable species, often confused with the C European 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A06271FD058B9EFFC40F849" authority="Suter (1802: 145)" authorityName="Suter" authorityPageNumber="145" authorityYear="1802" box="[556,915,1945,1972]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lachenalii">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD058B9EFFD6CF84E" box="[556,703,1945,1971]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">H. lachenalii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3B4A06271FD0BCB9ECFC40F849" author="Suter, J. R." box="[712,915,1945,1972]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" refId="ref3247" refString="Suter, J. R. (1802) Helvetiens Flora, 2. Orell &amp; Fussli, Zurich, 504 pp." type="book" year="1802">Suter (1802: 145)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and occurs in the whole Apennine range, with its centre of diversity in the C and N Apennine (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3B4A06271FD0DDB9C8FC62F82A" author="Gottschlich, G. &amp; Raimondo, F. M. &amp; Di Gristina, E." box="[681,945,1981,2007]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" pagination="826 - 831" refId="ref2869" refString="Gottschlich, G., Raimondo, F. M. &amp; Di Gristina, E. (2013) Hieracium pallidum subsp. aetnense (Asteraceae), a new subspecies from Sicily (Italy), with notes on the taxonomy of H. pallidum Biv. Plant Biosystems 147 (3): 826 - 831. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 11263504.2013.829882" type="journal article" year="2013">
Gottschlich 
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD140B9CBFCBEF82A" box="[820,877,1981,2007]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). Hybridisation processes of 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A06271FD68DB9CBFA7FF82A" authorityName="Belli" authorityYear="1897" box="[1273,1452,1982,2007]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grovesianum">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD68DB9CBFA7FF82A" box="[1273,1452,1982,2007]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">H. grovesianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A06271FD2CEB997FD53F801" authority="Willdenow (1803: 1588)" authorityName="Willdenow" authorityPageNumber="1588" authorityYear="1803" box="[186,640,2017,2044]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="racemosum">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD2CEB997FE8CF806" box="[186,351,2018,2043]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">H. racemosum</emphasis>
Willdenow (1803: 1588)
</taxonomicName>
with other local taxa have apparently resulted in a complex of similar morphotypes, which have recently been grouped together in 
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD15BB673FC98F7E2" box="[815,843,2054,2079]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">H.</emphasis>
sect G 
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A06271FD1ECB673FBD6F7E2" box="[920,1029,2054,2079]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">rovesiana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3B4A06271FD660B670FB37F7E2" author="Gottschlich, G." box="[1044,1252,2053,2079]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 328" refId="ref2675" refString="Gottschlich, G. (2009 a) Die Gattung Hieracium L. (Compositae) in der Region Abruzzen (Italien). Eine floristisch-taxonomische Studie. Stapfia 89: 1 - 328." type="journal article" year="2009">Gottschlich 2009a</bibRefCitation>
–c, 2011).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF2666424A012718D2FCBA5CFB44FBC3" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5147155" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5147155" box="[136,1175,1065,1087]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5147155/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" startId="4.[136,229,1065,1087]" targetBox="[227,1361,190,1041]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BE636CA4A012718D2FCBA5CFB44FBC3" blockId="4.[136,1175,1065,1087]" box="[136,1175,1065,1087]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A012718D2FCBA5CFF2DFBC3" bold="true" box="[136,254,1065,1087]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
Carbonate rocks and stony slopes of Scala di Gaudolino, the habitat of 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A012718D1D9BA5FFB42FBC2" authorityName="Di Grist., Gottschl. &amp; Raimondo" authorityYear="2014" box="[941,1169,1066,1087]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terraccianoi">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A012718D1D9BA5FFB42FBC2" box="[941,1169,1066,1087]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Hieracium terraccianoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BE636CA4A012718D2C9BA1BFF1CFB09" blockId="4.[136,1452,1133,1339]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">
Among the hitherto known taxa of 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A012718D015BA1BFC70FB75" box="[609,931,1134,1160]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Grovesiana">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A012718D015BA1BFD0AFB7A" box="[609,729,1134,1159]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Hieracium</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A012718D155BA1BFC70FB75" box="[801,931,1134,1160]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Grovesiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A012718D1C1BA1BFBB5FB7A" authorityName="Di Grist., Gottschl. &amp; Raimondo" authorityYear="2014" box="[949,1126,1134,1159]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terraccianoi">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A012718D1C1BA1BFBB5FB7A" box="[949,1126,1134,1159]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">H. terraccianoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles most closely the Sicilian endemic 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A012718D33ABAE7FB9BFB56" authority="Caldarella, Gianguzzi &amp; Gottschlich (2014: 439)" authorityName="Caldarella, Gianguzzi &amp; Gottschlich" authorityPageNumber="439" authorityYear="2014" box="[334,1096,1169,1195]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="busambarense">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A012718D33ABAE7FDC1FB56" box="[334,530,1169,1195]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">H. busambarense</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3B4A012718D06EBAE4FB9BFB56" author="Caldarella, O. &amp; Gianguzzi, L. &amp; Gottschlich, G." box="[538,1096,1169,1195]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" pagination="439 - 443" refId="ref2279" refString="Caldarella, O., Gianguzzi, L. &amp; Gottschlich, G. (2014) Hieracium busambarense, a new species of the sect. Grovesiana (Asteraceae) from Sicily (Italy). Plant Biosystems 148 (3): 439 - 443. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 11263504.2013.778352" type="journal article" year="2014">Caldarella, Gianguzzi &amp; Gottschlich (2014: 439)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but it differs from this species in having spotted leaves, less acute involucral bracts and by bract indumentum (more stellate hairs and less glandular hairs).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE636CA4A012718D2C9BA8BFA70FAC6" blockId="4.[136,1452,1133,1339]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A012718D2C9BA8BFE14FAEA" authorityName="Di Grist., Gottschl. &amp; Raimondo" authorityYear="2014" box="[189,455,1278,1303]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terraccianoi">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A012718D2C9BA8BFE14FAEA" box="[189,455,1278,1303]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Hieracium terraccianoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
adds to the considerable number of new endemic 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D494A012718D18ABA8BFBA5FAEA" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1022,1142,1278,1303]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92DEAD84A012718D18ABA8BFBA5FAEA" box="[1022,1142,1278,1303]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Hieracium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
